data.name: IIS Monitoring
data.description: View of key metrics relating to the advanced monitoring solution that provides unparalleled visibility into your web server's performance and application delivery

markdown.markdownText:
**IIS Monitoring **

IIS Monitoring is a robust observability solution that provides deep visibility into your Microsoft IIS (Internet Information Services) web server performance, enabling you to monitor and optimize web application delivery in real time. With IIS monitoring, you gain comprehensive insights into connection activity, request throughput, application pool health, caching efficiency, and WebSocket behavior—empowering you to detect service degradation, resource exhaustion, and configuration issues before they affect end users.

This dashboard is part of the out-of-the-box IIS extension, delivering real-time visibility into the health and performance of your IIS-hosted applications and infrastructure.

**Use Cases Covered**
* Global Service Overview 
* Client & Traffic Overview 
* Request & CGI/ISAPI Pipeline 
* Application Pool Monitoring
* Worker Process Health
* Worker Thread & WebSocket Tracking
* Caching – Worker Level
* Caching – Server Level 
   
**More about performance monitoring of IIS ** [here](https://github.com/prometheus-community/windows_exporter/blob/master/docs/collector.iis.md#metricsl)
